00:04:22.880 --> 00:04:34.880
But the good news to that is we view BS Lib at being at a stage now where we view it as superseding Shiny Dashboard.

00:04:34.880 --> 00:04:41.600
So a lot of the components that you use in Shiny Dashboard, you'll find modern replacements for BS Lib.

00:04:41.600 --> 00:04:47.200
So we have things like cards and sidebar layouts.

00:04:47.399 --> 00:05:00.079
And also things you won't find, like tooltips and popovers that will add some really nice additional functionality to your dashboards.

00:05:00.079 --> 00:05:07.760
And then, of course, you get all like sort of the rich theming infrastructure that comes with BS Lib as well.

00:05:07.760 --> 00:05:15.519
So but, you know, technically speaking, there was just some challenges with updating Shiny Dashboard from,

00:05:15.519 --> 00:05:20.760
you know, it uses this framework called Admin LTE, which was built on Bootstrap 3.

00:05:20.760 --> 00:05:27.040
So bringing up both of those dependencies to modern versions, there was just kind of some technical complexity with that,

00:05:27.040 --> 00:05:34.480
where we decided to kind of go in a different direction where we decided that we would actually kind of build out these components in BS Lib

00:05:34.480 --> 00:05:43.519
instead of depending on a framework that was struggling to keep up to speed with modern practices.

00:05:43.519 --> 00:05:49.359
So I know there is a few things, probably the biggest thing is sidebar navigation.

00:05:49.359 --> 00:05:58.000
I think I've seen at least one question about this, where we don't have an answer for, you know, with Shiny Dashboard,

00:05:58.000 --> 00:06:05.480
